               <head>Miscellany of verse and prose</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4068-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled, illuminated <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">bayāz̤</term> or notebook of Persian and Arabic analecta assembled from the works of (but not limited to) "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_98930150" role="ant">Rūmī</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_100210377" role="ant">Khayyām</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_56731778" role="ant">Ḥāfiẓ</persName>," <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f288" role="ant">Ibrāhīm "Adham</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_57523601" role="ant">Bīdil</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7674" role="ant">Bihjat</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_91000370" role="ant">Ṣāʾib</persName>," <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_26833521" role="ant">Nāṣir ʿAlī "Nāṣir</persName>," <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7719" role="ant">Muḥammad Qāsim</persName>, "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7743" role="ant">Shādmān</persName>," "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_14200302" role="ant">Āṣafī" ʿAjamī</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7709" role="ant">Mīrzā Nāṣir "Inṣāf</persName>," <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7720" role="ant">Muḥammad Qāsim Mashhadī</persName>, in addition to some compositions by compilers / calligraphers
                        </p>
                        <p>Each folio or side is transcribed by different writers at different 1) dates and 2) places, at the request of a certain <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7697" role="pat">Mawlānā Muḥammad Yūsuf</persName> (f. 27r), <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7708" role="pat">Mīrzā Muḥammad Yūsuf</persName> (f. 35v), or <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7672" role="pat">Āqā Muḥammad Yūsuf-jīv</persName> (f. 58r)
                        </p>
                        <p>Dates range widely from the <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">ghurrah</term> or <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1 Ramaz̤ān of regnal year 43 (ʿĀlamgīr I)</date> at <name type="place">Fort Satara</name> (f. 27r) to <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">Wednesday 23 Jumādá I 1087</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1676</date> (f. 29v)
                        </p>
                        <p>The manuscript additionally preserves a rare letter (f. 64r) from the Timurid or Mughal Prince <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656959.0x000001 viaf_27879596" role="aut">Dārā Shukūh</persName> addressed to the itinerant Iranian Jewish mystic, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_297150869791122190002" role="rcp">Muḥammad Saʿīd Kāshānī "Sarmad"</persName> (see IO Islamic 4059 for his poems)
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara" xml:lang="per">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
