                     <summary>Transcribed by more than 8 hands ranging in quality and style of script: calligraphic <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">nastaʿlīq</term>, rough nastaʿlīq,
                     </summary>
                     <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">
                        <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">shikastah</term>, <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">shikastah āmīz</term>, <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">shafīʿah</term>, Indian <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">taʿliq</term>, <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">naskh</term>, etc, written at an oblique angle. Various scribe mentioned (in signatures) by name: <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7783" role="scr">Muḥammad Riz̤āʾ</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7774" role="scr">Sayyid Yūsuf Aḥmad or Sayyid Yūsuf Aḥmad al-Ḥusaynī</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7766" role="scr">ʿAli Bilgrāmī</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7775" role="scr">Shaykh Ḥabīb</persName>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
